uima.cas.Sofa.sofaString: 150,"cect scan thorax dated- 18.12.2013 contrast enhanced scan of the thorax has been performed. case of ca lung, on follow up, comparison is done with previous ct dated 03/09/2013. volume loss is noted in the right hemithorax with collapse of the upper lobe and ipsilateral shift of mediastinum is seen the previously seen right hilar mass and distal collapse consolidation has slightly increased from previous scan. however the mass cannot be well differentiated from each other. subcm nodules in the right lower lobe- appear unchanged. severe centilobular emphysematous changes are also seen in the both lungs, predominantly the upper lobe along with paraseptal emphysema - unchanged enlarged nodes are seen in the superior mediastinum, right paratracheal, ap window, prevascular regions , largest measuring 2.4 x 2.0 cm- unchanged as compared with the previous scan. the pleural spaces are clear. the trachea & left main stem bronchi are normal. the heart & mediastinal great vessels appear normal. few subcm hypodense lesions are seen in the liver unchanged. no e/o destructive bone lesions. case of ca lung, on follow up, comparison has been done with previous scan dated 03/09/2013 the previously seen right hilar mass and distal collapse consolidation has slightly increased from previous scan. however the mass cannot be well differentiated from each other. subcm nodules in the right lower lobe- appear unchanged. severe centilobular emphysematous changes are also seen in the both lungs, predominantly the upper lobe along with paraseptal emphysema - unchanged the mediastinal adenopathy is unchanged."
